gnupg-pkcs11-scd -- PKCS#11 enabled gnupg scd.

Copyright (c) 2006 Zeljko Vrba <zvrba@globalnet.hr>
Copyright (c) 2006 Alon Bar-Lev <alon.barlev@gmail.com>

*************************************************************************

For the latest version go to:
	http://gnupg-pkcs11.sourceforge.net/

To build and install:
	./configure
	make
	make install

*************************************************************************

Operating Systems:
	POSIX compliant, WIN32

Dependencies:
	libgpg-error>=1.3
		http://www.gnupg.org
	libassuan>=0.9.2
		http://www.gnupg.org
	libgcrypt>=1.2.2
		http://www.gnupg.org
	or (
		openssl>=0.9.7
			http://www.openssl.org
		gnutls>=1.4.4
			http://www.gnutls.org
	)
	pthread (nptl)
	dl

*************************************************************************

WIN32

Supported single threaded server mode.
Implementing multi-threaded server forces copy of win32 socket handling
from gnupg, and it is GPLed. When libassuan will handle sockets we will
be able to implement it.

Compiling:
	Using cross compiler MinGW

	w32root=/tmp/gpg-win32; \
	./configure --prefix=/ --host=mingw32 \
		--with-libgpg-error-prefix=${w32root} \
		--with-libassuan-prefix=${w32root} \
		--with-libgcrypt-prefix=${w32root} \
		PKG_CONFIG=true \
		OPENSSL_CFLAGS="-I${w32root}/include" OPENSSL_LIBS="-L${w32root} -lcrypto"

*************************************************************************

